The dark J-V curves of devices are shown in Fig. 5e. The DIB/TA/SVA device shows reduced reverse saturated current densities, indicating improved diode characteristics with a low leaking current. In the forward direction, the DIB/TA/SVA device shows an early transition from Ohmic to semiconductor zones and higher saturation value, indicating a higher charge density41,42. The calculated rectification ratios (frec) at ±1.0 V are 4.8 × 102, 7.6 × 103, and 7.1 × 104 for as-cast, DIB, and DIB/TA/SVA devices, respectively, which is in consistence with the FFs43. The fundamental electronic property of the blended thin films is studied by the electron density of state (DoS) characterization, following the relationship of3gnE=NtEtexp−E−ELUMOEt\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
